The paper deals with distributed computing, specifically in the LOCAL model, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves graph theory and graph problems, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The concept of symmetry-breaking is a common theme in distributed computing, which could place the paper in the sub-category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves lower bounds, which could suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of Learning (cs.LG) or Information Theory (cs.IT).
